},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"copyist, scribe (person who makes manual copies of works)"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the active participle of نَسَخَ (nasaḵa, “to copy”)."},"ipa":["/naː.six/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n39733","headword_ar":"نَاسِخٌ","root":"nsx","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"munotasixN","text_ar":"مُنْتَسِخٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A copier,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"transcriber, of a writing"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"writings,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a book"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"books."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=yapN naAsixapN","text_ar":"ا=يَةٌ نَاسِخَةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A verse of the Kur-án that abrogates, annuls,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"supersedes, another verse."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) [See 1.] [And so,] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=yapN manosuwxapN","text_ar":"ا=يَةٌ مَنْسُوخَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A verse of the Kur-án that is abrogated, annulled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"superseded, by another verse."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) ―         -b3-  ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAsixN","text_ar":"نَاسِخٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"An epithet applied to a particle, (namely,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~a","text_ar":"اـِنَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the like, and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA","text_ar":"مَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lA","text_ar":"لا"},{"kind":"text","text":",) or a verb, (namely, the abstract"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAn","text_ar":"كَان"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the like, and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAda","text_ar":"كَادَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the like, and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zan~a","text_ar":"ظَنَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the like,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which effects a change of the grammatical form,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the meaning, in a nominal proposition before which it is placed."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alxuruwfu AlnAsixapu liloA_ibotidaA='i","text_ar":"الخُرُوفُ الناسِخَةُ لِلْاـِبْتِدَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The particles which annul the quality of the inchoative."},{"kind":"text","text":"]"}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D9%86%D8%A7%D8%B3%D8%AE/","headword_ar":"ناسخ","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_48","lexicon_en":"Sultan Qaboos Encyclopedia of Arab Names (Sultan Qaboos University, 1985)","lexicon_ar":"موسوعة السلطان قابوس لأسماء العرب","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=118358#c30dab","body_html":"ناسخ<br>من (ن س خ) من يعيد كتابة الكتب، ومن يغير الشيء ويزيله.<br>ناسخ<br>عن العبرية ناسيخ بمعنى أمير وحاكم ووالي. يستخدم للذكور."}]}}